dct_title_s: A map of the Lower Ohio Valley : showing the city of Evansville to be the centre of a territory richer than the valley of the Nile in agricultural products, and in the very heart of the great coal and iron deposits of the west and southwest
dct_description_sm: D.J. Lake & Co., published by the Evansville, Indiana Courier Company. Shows portions of Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, and Tennessee. Includes location map. At bottom left: Copyright, 1879, by Evansville Courier Co. At bottom center: Engraved by Crosscup & West, Philada. At bottom right: D.J. Lake & Co., 27 S. Sixth St., Philada.
Dimensions: 36 x 36 cm, on sheet 49 x 46 cm; Scale: Scale not given.
